===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Paracelsus|Paracelsus]] for a tincture he made containing opium < {{etyl|NL.}} < {{etyl|la}} {{term|laudare||to praise|lang=la}}, or {{term|ladanum||a gum resin|lang=la}} < {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|λάδανον||tr=ladanon|lang=grc}}. Originally the same word as {{term|ladanum}}, {{term|ladbdanum}}, compare French {{term|laudanum|lang=fr}}, Italian {{term|laudano|lang=it}}, {{term|ladano|lang=it}}. See {{term|ladanum}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A [[tincture]] of [[opium]], once widely used for various [[medical]] purposes and as a [[recreational drug]].

